Vice President Biden met with Latvian Prime Minister Laimdota Straujuma at the White House. They discussed the United States' commitment to the defense of NATO allies under Article 5 and thanked the US for its support in Latvia's security. They also talked about the situation in Ukraine and the need for the US and Europe to remain united in confronting Russia's actions. They discussed the importance of coordinating actions among European states to bolster Europe's energy security. They agreed on the importance of the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (TTIP) in creating jobs and supporting economic growth.